<br>
<h2>Privacy first</h2>
<p>By default, all notes and media are stored on your iPhone, entirely offline.
<br>
<br></p>
<h2>A familiar interface</h2>
<p>Browse your entries chronologically through a familiar micro-blogging-like feed (similar to <a href="https://twitter.com">Twitter</a>, <a href="https://mastodon.social">Mastodon</a>, or <a href="https://bsky.app">Bluesky</a>).</p>
<p>Save notes or journal entries like you would post to any of these familiar services.</p>
<p>With Journelly, your data is yours and remains fully offline.
<br>
<br></p>
<h2>iCloud syncing (optional)</h2>
<p>While Journelly is offline by default, you may optionally sync with other devices via iCloud.</p>
<p>Some folks have used <a href="https://workingcopy.app">Working Copy</a>, <a href="https://github.com/pixelspark/sushitrain">Sushitrain</a>, or <a href="https://mobiussync.com">M√∂bius Sync</a> to sync though your mileage may vary. As of v1, I can only offer iCloud as the officially supported provider.
<br>
<br></p>
<h2>No lock-in (org plain text)</h2>
<p>Journelly stores your entries as a plain text file, using <a href="https://orgmode.org/worg/org-syntax.html">org markup</a> to structure things.</p>
<p>If you're unfamiliar with <a href="https://orgmode.org/worg/org-syntax.html">org markup</a>, no worries. It's just what's under the hood. Journelly offers a familiar interface to interact with your entries.</p>
<p>If you're still curious, this is what the marked up text looks like:</p>
<br>
<pre><code>* [2025-04-03 Thu 20:41] @ Distillery Lane
:PROPERTIES:
:LATITUDE: 51.488644146827866
:LONGITUDE: -0.22292387343051026
:WEATHER_TEMPERATURE: 8.69¬∞C
:WEATHER_CONDITION: Rain
:WEATHER_SYMBOL: cloud.rain
:END:

- [X] Try out Pad Thai Story in Hammersmith

[[file:Journelly.org.assets/images/4F0F3923-675A-461E-9B02-63CEDE76C765.jpg]]

* [2025-04-02 Wed 15:41] @ Charing Cross Road
:PROPERTIES:
:LATITUDE: 51.51432060230237
:LONGITUDE: -0.1297243012637992
:WEATHER_TEMPERATURE: 13.84¬∞C
:WEATHER_CONDITION: Mostly Cloudy
:WEATHER_SYMBOL: cloud
:END:
Check out &quot;Take on me&quot; remix by speed 45 #music

https://youtube.com/watch?v=vM5ds851QqU&amp;feature=shared
</code></pre>
<br>
<br>
<h2>Markdown is coming, want it sooner?</h2>
<p>Journelly's plain text format isn't surfaced to app users and kept as an implementation detail. While many users are happy to just use the app without thinking of internals, others are keen to poke at its plain text file from their beloved editors. Today, Journelly is powered by <a href="https://orgmode.org/worg/org-syntax.html">org markup</a>, but it will support Markdown in the future.</p>
<p>Please <a href="mailto:journelly+markdown@xenodium.com?subject=I'm%20interested%20Markdown%20for%20Journelly&amp;body=Just%20want%20to%20register%20my%20interest%20in%20Markdown%20support%20for%20Journelly.">register your interest</a>. The more requests I get, the sooner I'll get Markdown support out the door.
<br>
<br></p>
<h2>Journelly v1 is only the beginning</h2>
<p>I've got lots of wonderful feature requests in the pipeline. While I would have loved to squeeze more features into v1, I really needed to manage scope to be able to make its first launch. Having said that, v1 is only the beginning. I'm looking forward to bringing new features in. Many of them I really want for myself!</p>
<br>
<h2>Features</h2>
<p>I hope you find Journelly frictionless, simple, and intuitive to use. Please let me know if there are ways it can improve by reaching out through the app's feedback menu.</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/feedback.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Swipe gestures (edit/delete/share)</h2>
<p>Swipe right to expose edit and share actions.</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/swipe-right.png" width=50%></center>
<p>Swipe left to delete items.</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/swipe-left.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Editing</h2>
<p>In addition to entering text, the following items can be added from the edit dialog.</p>
<ul>
<li>Checkboxes</li>
<li>Images</li>
<li>Lists</li>
<li>Location</li>
<li>Timestamps</li>
<li>Weather</li>
</ul>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/new.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Sharing in</h2>
<p>Journelly can receive text, links, and images from other iOS apps.</p>
<h2>Sharing out</h2>
<ul>
<li>Share an entry: swipe right and select &quot;Share&quot; option.</li>
<li>Share an image: Use the &quot;...&quot; menu on the image.</li>
<li>Share entry links: long tap on link to view options.</li>
</ul>
<h2>View markup</h2>
<p>Internally, Journelly is powered by plain text org markup. You can view internal markup by toggling via the menu.</p>
<h2>Link previews</h2>
<p>Links in entries are automatically previewed</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/links.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Storage</h2>
<p>Journelly offers 3 types of storage locations:</p>
<ul>
<li>In-app: Your data remains entirely offline and within the app. This offers most privacy, but please backup regularly using the archive menu optoin.</li>
<li>iCloud: Your data is automatically synced with all other Apple devices.</li>
<li>Other: Choose an alternate location on your device (outside the app).</li>
</ul>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/storage.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Backups</h2>
<p>Please backup your data regularly. You can create backup .zip archives via the menu, including all entries and assets.</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/archive.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Hashtags</h2>
<p>Hashtags are recognized and can be tapped on to search for other items including the same hashtag.</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/hashtag-search.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Home location</h2>
<p>Long tap on an entry's location to designate it as your &quot;Home&quot; location. Instead of showing the street address, it'll display as &quot;Home&quot;.</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/home.jpg" width=50%></center>
<h2>Pull to reload</h2>
<p>Want to force a reload? Pull to reload.</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/pull-reload.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Revert to snapshots</h2>
<p>For peace of mind, Journelly keeps text snapshots of your data within the app and offline for up to 14 days (excluding media). You can revert to a previous snapshot at any time from the menu.</p>
<center><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/journelly-for-ios/revert.png" width=50%></center>
<h2>Shortcuts</h2>
<h3>Open Journelly</h3>
<p>You may use <code>journelly://</code> to open the app.</p>
<h3>Create new entry</h3>
<p>You may use <code>journelly://new?body=hello</code> to create a new entry.</p>
<h2>Privacy policy</h2>
<p>No personal data is sent to any server, as there is no server component to this app. There are neither third party server integrations, accounts, analytics, advertising, nor hidden trackers in this app. All your data is kept on your iPhone, unless you choose a cloud provider to sync or store your data. See your cloud provider's privacy policy for details on how they may handle it.</p>
<h2>Enjoy Journelly</h2>
<p>I hope you enjoy using Journelly! - <a href="https://xenodium.com">√Ålvaro</a></p>
